sql:
SELECT project_id
FROM projects
WHERE delivery_status = 'Completed' AND budget > (SELECT AVG(budget) FROM projects);

SELECT DISTINCT username
FROM users
WHERE active_status = 'active';

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_essential_projects
FROM projects
WHERE priority = 'Essential';

SELECT project_id, blueprint
FROM projects
WHERE budget > (
    SELECT AVG(budget)
    FROM projects
);

SELECT project_id, blueprint
FROM projects
WHERE budget = (SELECT MAX(budget) FROM projects);

SELECT AVG(CAST(REPLACE(trim(budget, '$'), ',', '') AS REAL)) AS average_budget
FROM projects
WHERE priority = 'High';

external_knowledge:
Sailing to the shore of completion: metaphorically refers to projects reaching a fully implemented state where both the overall project and its individual tasks are marked as 'Implemented'.;
Delivery status '11 Implemented': indicates the project as a whole has reached its final stage of implementation.;
Task status 'Implemented': signifies that all individual tasks within the project are also completed and implemented.

